'''Dženis Burnić''' ({{IPA|bs|dʒêːnis bǔrnitɕ|pron}}; born 22 May 1998) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[2. Bundesliga]] club [[Karlsruher SC]]. Born in Germany, he plays for the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

Burnić started his professional career at [[Borussia Dortmund]], playing mainly in its [[Borussia Dortmund II|reserve team]], before being loaned to [[VfB Stuttgart]] in 2017 and to [[Dynamo Dresden]] in 2019. The following year, he signed with [[1. FC Heidenheim]]. In 2023, he moved to Karlsruher SC.

A former German youth international, Burnić made his senior international debut for Bosnia and Herzegovina in 2024, earning 20 [[Cap (sport)|caps]] since.

==Club career==

===Borussia Dortmund===
Burnić started playing football at a local club, before joining [[Borussia Dortmund Youth Sector|Borussia Dortmund's youth academy]] in 2006. In April 2015, he signed his first professional contract with the team.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/dzenis-burnic-u-borussiji-dortmund-do-2018-godine/150423004|title=Dženis Burnić potpisao u Borussiji Dortmund do 2018. godine|website=klix.ba|date=23 April 2015|access-date=23 April 2015|language=bs}}</ref> He made his professional debut in a [[2016–17 UEFA Champions League#Group F|UEFA Champions League]] game against [[Sporting CP]] on 18 October 2016 at the age of 18.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oslobodjenje.ba/sport/fudbal/ino-fudbal/evropska-takmicenja/dzenis-burnic-debitovao-za-prvi-tim-borussije-dortmund-69839|title=Dženis Burnić debitovao za prvi tim Borussije Dortmund|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=18 October 2016|access-date=21 October 2016|language=bs}}</ref> Four months later, he made his league debut against [[SV Darmstadt 98|SV Darmstadt]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/276535/potencijalni-zmaj-debitirao-za-dortmund-u-bundesligi|title=Potencijalni Zmaj debitirao za Dortmund u Bundesligi|website=avaz.ba|date=11 February 2017|access-date=14 February 2017|language=bs}}</ref>

In July, Burnić was sent on a season-long loan to [[VfB Stuttgart]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fokus.ba/sport/fudbal/dzenis-burnic-presao-u-stuttgart/789087|title=Dženis Burnić prešao u Stuttgart|website=fokus.ba|date=11 July 2017|access-date=14 July 2017|language=bs}}</ref>

In January 2019, he was loaned to [[Dynamo Dresden]] for the remainder of the campaign. In July, his loan was extended for an additional season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/potencijalni-reprezentativac-bih-na-novoj-posudbi|title=Potencijalni reprezentativac BiH na novoj posudbi|website=sportske.ba|date=1 July 2019|access-date=1 July 2019|language=bs}}</ref> On 3 May, he scored his first professional goal against [[FC St. Pauli]], which secured the victory for his squad.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/275484-burnic-prvijencem-donio-pobjedu-dynamo-dresdenu-i-rijesio-ga-brige-oko-opstanka|title=Burnić prvijencem donio pobjedu Dynamo Dresdenu i riješio ga brige oko opstanka|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=3 May 2019|access-date=3 May 2019|language=bs}}</ref>

===1. FC Heidenheim===
In August 2020, Burnić moved to [[1. FC Heidenheim]] on a three-year deal.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://kicker.de/heidenheim-holt-burnic-von-borussia-dortmund-780980/artikel|title=Heidenheim holt Burnic von Borussia Dortmund|website=kicker.de|date=3 August 2020|access-date=3 August 2020|language=de}}</ref> On 21 November, he made his official debut for the side against [[Holstein Kiel]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://kicker.de/kiel-gegen-heidenheim-2020-bundesliga-4667422/analyse|title=Doppelschlag kurz vor Schluss: Kühlwetter bringt Heidenheim ersten Auswärtspunkt|website=kicker.de|date=21 November 2020|access-date=21 November 2020|language=de}}</ref> He won his first title with 1. FC Heidenheim, club's first trophy ever, on 28 May 2023, when they were crowned league champions, which earned them promotion to the [[2023–24 Bundesliga|Bundesliga]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://kicker.de/heidenheim-steigt-dramatisch-auf-und-schickt-den-hsv-in-die-relegation-bielefeld-muss-nachsitzen-953160/artikel|title=Heidenheim steigt dramatisch auf und schickt den HSV in die Relegation: Bielefeld muss nachsitzen|website=kicker.de|date=28 May 2023|access-date=28 May 2023|language=de}}</ref>

===Karlsruher SC===
In July, Burnić switched to [[Karlsruher SC]] on a one-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://kicker.de/etwas-ganz-grosses-entsteht-ksc-verpflichtet-ex-dortmunder-burnic-959608/artikel|title=Etwas ganz Großes entsteht: KSC verpflichtet Ex-Dortmunder Burnic|website=kicker.de|date=17 July 2023|access-date=18 July 2023|language=de}}</ref> He made his competitive debut for the squad on 29 July against [[VfL Osnabrück]] and managed to score a goal, ensuring the triumph for his team.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://kicker.de/osnabrueck-gegen-karlsruhe-2023-bundesliga-4861667/analyse|title=Burnics Distanzschuss lässt Karlsruhe spät jubeln|website=kicker.de|date=29 July 2023|access-date=1 August 2023|language=de}}</ref>

In April 2024, he signed a new multi-year deal with Karlsruher SC.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://kicker.de/neuer-vertrag-konstante-burnic-verlaengert-in-karlsruhe-1016740/artikel|title=Neuer Vertrag: Konstante Burnic verlängert in Karlsruhe|website=kicker.de|date=18 April 2024|access-date=21 April 2024|language=de}}</ref>

==International career==
Despite representing [[Germany national football team|Germany]] at all youth levels, Burnić decided to play for [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] at the senior level.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/burnic-presretan-nakon-debija-bih-je-drzava-koju-volim-i-ponosan-sam-sto-sam-dio-ove-price/240606065|title=Burnić presretan nakon debija: BiH je država koju volim i ponosan sam što sam dio ove priče|website=klix.ba|date=6 June 2024|access-date=7 June 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

In May 2024, his request to change sports citizenship from German to Bosnian was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oslobodjenje.ba/sport/fudbal/reprezentacija/spahic-govorio-o-gigovicu-djuricu-jasicu-ali-i-drugima-posao-nece-biti-lagan-954702|title=Spahić govorio o Gigoviću, Đuriću, Jašiću, ali i drugima: Posao neće biti lagan|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=16 May 2024|access-date=17 May 2024|language=bs}}</ref> Later that month, he received his first senior call up, for [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] games against [[England national football team|England]] and [[Italy national football team|Italy]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/ovo-je-barbarezov-spisak-za-englesku-i-italiju-pozvano-sedam-novih-zmajeva/545686|title=Ovo je Barbarezov spisak za Englesku i Italiju: Pozvano sedam novih Zmajeva|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=16 May 2024|access-date=18 May 2024|language=bs}}</ref> He debuted against the former on 3 June.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/engleska-slavila-protiv-bih-zmajevi-u-barbarezovom-debiju-za-pola-sata-potopljeni-u-newcastleu/189628|title=Engleska slavila protiv BiH: Zmajevi u Barbarezovom debiju za pola sata potopljeni u Newcastleu|website=faktor.ba|date=3 June 2024|access-date=4 June 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

In June 2026, Burnić was named in Bosnia and Herzegovina's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/barbarez-poslao-konacan-spisak-fifa-i-jedno-ime-otputovalo-u-ameriku-ali-nije-na-listi|title=Barbarez poslao konačan spisak FIFA-i: Jedno ime otputovalo u Ameriku, ali nije na listi|website=sportske.ba|date=3 June 2026|access-date=3 June 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Burnić married his long-time girlfriend Danijela in June 2023. Together they have a son.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/cs-magazin/ljubav-veze/stigla-beba-zmaj-dobio-svog-nasljednika/240653|title=Stigla beba: Zmaj dobio svog nasljednika|website=faktor.ba|date=26 December 2026|access-date=28 December 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

He is a practising [[Islam|Muslim]]; together with international teammates [[Amar Dedić]], [[Ermedin Demirović]] and [[Tarik Muharemović]] he visited a [[mosque]] in [[Sarajevo]] during the national team's concentration.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/zmajevi-snimljeni-na-dzumi-dedic-demirovic-muharemovic-i-burnic-bili-u-dzamiji-u-sarajevu/639157|title=Zmajevi snimljeni na džumi: Dedić, Demirović, Muharemović i Burnić bili u džamiji u Sarajevu|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=29 May 2026|access-date=1 June 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

